# Next.js Architecture

We are using Next.js for our frontend application.

## Routing System
<% if (options.router === 'app') { %>
- **CRITICAL**: We are using the modern **App Router** (Next.js 13+).
- ALL pages, layouts, and API routes must be placed inside the `src/app` directory.
- Use `page.tsx` for UI boundaries and `route.ts` for API endpoints.
- Do NOT use the `pages/` directory.
- Default to React Server Components. Only use `"use client"` when interactivity (hooks, state) is strictly required.
<% } else { %>
- **CRITICAL**: We are using the legacy **Pages Router**.
- ALL pages and API routes must be placed inside the `src/pages` directory.
- Do NOT use the `app/` directory.
- Use `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps` for data fetching.
<% } %>

## Project Structure
- `src/components`: Reusable UI components.
- `src/lib`: Utility functions and shared logic.
- `src/hooks`: Custom React hooks.
- `src/types`: TypeScript interfaces and types.
